18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 76 O.S. 2021, Section 19, is
20 amended to read as follows:
21 Section 19. A. 1. Any person who is or has been a patient of
22 a doctor, hospital or other medical institution health care provider
23 or health care facility, or such person’s personal representative,
24 shall, as provided under 45 C.F.R., Section 164.502, be entitled,
Req. No. 17479 Page 1

1 upon request, to obtain access to the information contained in the
2 patient’s medical records including any x-ray or other photograph or
3 image, pathology slide, or the patient’s medical bills.
4 2. Disclosure of the information described in paragraph 1 of
5 this subsection regarding a deceased patient shall require either a
6 court order or a written release of an executor, administrator, or
7 personal representative appointed by the court, or if there is no
8 such appointment, by the spouse of the patient or, if none, by any
9 responsible member of the family of the patient. As used in this
10 paragraph, “responsible family member” shall mean the parent, adult
11 child, adult sibling, or other adult relative who was actively
12 involved in providing care to or monitoring the care of the patient
13 as verified by the doctor, hospital or other medical institution
14 health care provider or health care facility responsible for the
15 care and treatment of such person.
16 2. Any person who is or has been a patient of a doctor,
17 hospital or other medical institution shall be furnished copies of
18 all medical records including any x-ray, other photograph or image,
19 pathology slide or all medical bills pertaining to that person’s
20 case upon request and upon the tender of the expenses enumerated in
21 this paragraph. The cost of each copy to such person or to the
22 personal representative, spouse or responsible family member of such
23 person, not including any x-ray or other photograph or image or
24 pathology slide, shall be fifty cents ($0.50) for each page.
Req. No. 17479 Page 2

1 3. A health care provider or health care facility may impose a
2 reasonable, cost-based fee when patients or their personal
3 representatives request copies of medical records; provided, that
4 the fee includes only the cost of applicable expenses listed in 42
5 C.F.R., Section 164.524(c)(4).
6 4. Requests for medical records and medical bills from, or
7 directed to, attorneys, insurance companies, other third parties,
8 and by way of subpoena shall be charged a base fee of Twenty Dollars
9 ($20.00) not more than Twenty-five Dollars ($25.00) in addition to
10 the a per page charges required pursuant to this section fee of:
11 a. not more than seventy cents ($0.70) for paper copies,
12 plus postage or delivery fee, or
13 b. not more than forty cents ($0.40) for electronic
14 copies.
15 The base fee shall be charged regardless of whether any records
16 related to the request are located. A fee of not more than Fifteen
17 Dollars ($15.00) shall be charged if a certification or an affidavit
18 by the provider regarding the authenticity of the medical records or
19 bills is requested. The physician, hospital or other medical
20 professionals and institutions, or their business associates as the
21 term is defined in Section 160.103 of Title 45 of the United States
22 Code of Federal Regulations shall produce the records in digital
23 form at the rate of thirty cents ($0.30) per page if:
24
Req. No. 17479 Page 3

1 a. the entire request can be reproduced from an
2 electronic health record system,
3 b. the records are specifically requested to be delivered
4 in electronic format, and
5 c. the records can be delivered electronically.
6 If a provider or business associate transmits the records
7 electronically, no postage shall be charged but a delivery charge
8 shall apply. In no event shall a charge for the reproduction of
9 electronically stored and delivered medical records pursuant to this
10 paragraph exceed Two Hundred Dollars ($200.00) Two Hundred Seventy
11 Dollars ($270.00) plus postage or delivery fee. The cost of each
12 printed x-ray, other photograph, or image to such person or to the
